Privacy Notice
Who is responsible for the processing of your data?
The purpose of this privacy policy (hereinafter, the "
Privacy Policy
") is to provide you, in a transparent manner, with all relevant information regarding how we treat your personal data. The Privacy Policy applies to all personal data that you provide to TESA ASSA ABLOY, Talleres de Escoriaza S.A., with registered offices at Barrio de Ventas, 35, 20305, Irún (hereinafter, "
TESA ASSA ABLOY
"), which is part of ASSA ABLOY Group, through the forms made available to you at
www.tesa.es
(hereinafter "
the Website
") or that we may obtain as a result of your interaction with us through the Website.
If you have any questions or need regarding data protection, you can contact us at the following
contact form.
For what purpose do we process your personal data?
You are hereby informed that TESA ASSA ABLOY will treat the personal data you provide through the online forms or during subsequent communications between you and TESA ASSA ABLOY in an appropriate, relevant and not excessive manner according to the specific, explicit and legitimate
purposes
for which they were obtained. In particular, TESA ASSA ABLOY will process the personal data for the following purposes, to the extent that there is a legal basis for each processing activity as explained below:
(a)   To manage the requests sent by the user, including requests for information regarding, for example, the products marketed by us, the products and/or services purchased by you, etc.
(b)   To manage access and use of the "Customer Area”. In particular, your personal data will be processed in order to provide you with access to the private area of the Website, the "Customer Area".
(c)   To administer and improve the Website by performing statistics on your use of the Website in order to understand how the Website is used so that we can improve your experience.
What is the legitimacy for the processing of your personal data?
The
legal basis
for the processing of data for purposes (a) and (b) is the
execution of the terms and conditions of the Website
.
The
legal basis
for processing the data for purpose (c) is the
legitimate interest
of TESA ASSA ABLOY in detecting areas for improvement and optimisation of the functionalities offered through the Website. We have made a prior analysis to ensure that TESA ASSA ABLOY's legitimate interest in this matter does not impact on the rights and freedoms of the user, so if you are interested in learning more about this, please contact us.
TESA ASSA ABLOY will collect and process the personal data provided by you through the contact form. You acknowledge and agree that failure to provide certain personal data will prevent TESA ASSA ABLOY from providing all services related to such data. Under no circumstances will TESA ASSA ABLOY illegitimately cede or exploit this data or use it for any purpose other than that expressly stated herein.
For how long do we keep your personal data?
TESA ASSA ABLOY
will retain
your personal data for as long as is necessary to manage your relationship with TESA ASSA ABLOY, either through (i) your use of the "Customer Area" and/or (ii) your request for information. In addition, TESA ASSA ABLOY will process your personal data to send you commercial communications to which you have subscribed until such time as you unsubscribe or cancel your subscription. When we process your personal data for the purpose of administering and improving the Website, we will process your personal data in a timely manner during the time in which we are taking the specific actions.
This means that your personal data will not be kept for longer than is necessary for the purposes described above, without prejudice to the retention of such data as may be necessary for the establishment, exercise or defence of potential claims and/or as permitted by applicable law. Once the possible actions have been prescribed in each case, we will proceed to erase the data.
Who has access to your personal data?
An optimal provision of the service that TESA ASSA ABLOY offers through its website may require other
third-party service providers
of TESA ASSA ABLOY to access the user's personal data as processors in order to provide services related to the Website. In particular, TESA ASSA ABLOY requires the services of data hosting providers.
In addition to the foregoing, you understand that TESA ASSA ABLOY may assign or communicate personal data to meet its obligations to the Public Administrations in the cases required under current legislation at any time and where appropriate, and also to other bodies such as the State Security Forces and Bodies and to judicial bodies.
What are your rights?
TESA ASSA ABLOY informs you about the possibility of exercising your rights of
access, rectification, opposition, deletion, portability and limitation of the processing
of personal data collected by TESA ASSA ABLOY.
These rights may be exercised free of charge by you and, where applicable, by your representative, by means of a signed written request sent to the following address: Barrio de Ventas, 35, 20305, Irún. This request must include the following information: your name and surname, address for notification purposes, photocopy of your National Identity Card or Passport, and the specifics of your request. In the case of representation, this must be demonstrated by means of a reliable document.You can also exercise these rights through the
privacy contact form
In addition to the above rights, you have the right to
withdraw your consent
at any time using the procedure described above, without such withdrawal of consent affecting the lawfulness of the processing prior to the withdrawal of your consent. TESA ASSA ABLOY may continue to process your data to the extent permitted by applicable law.
TESA ASSA ABLOY reminds you that you have the right to
file a complaint with the relevant supervisory authority
.
Who and where is your personal data transferred to?
We may transfer your personal data for the purposes set out above:
To organisations of the ASSA ABLOY Group, including but not limited to our brands such as ABLOY, Mul-T-Lock or Yale, that market, sell and support our solutions in Spain.
To third parties who provide services connected to our website or its functions, but only to the extent necessary to provide these services:
IT (Information Technology) providers who may host, develop and offer support for our products and websites
Digital Analytics providers who provide us with tools that help us improve your experience on our website
When required by law; and/or
To a buyer or potential buyer of our business.
Some recipients are located in countries outside the EU/European Economic Area (EEA). As in some cases these countries have a lower level of protection than that within the EU/EEA, when transferring personal data to countries outside the EU/EEA we use standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission to ensure a sufficient level of protection for your personal data. These standard contractual clauses can be found at
ec.europa.eu
.
We take measures to protect all personal data transferred to a third party, or to other countries, in accordance with applicable data protection laws and as stated above.
What security measures have we implemented?
TESA ASSA ABLOY undertakes to comply with its obligation of secrecy of personal data and its duty to keep them and will take the necessary measures to prevent their alteration, loss, unauthorised access or processing, in accordance with the provisions of applicable legislation.
From what age can you access our products and services?
The Website is
not intended for children under the age of 18
. By accepting that you have understood this Privacy Policy
you declare and guarantee that you are 18 years of age or older
.
Use of cookies
Our website uses cookies to distinguish you from other users of our website, which helps us to provide you with a good experience when you browse our Website and also allows us to improve it. You can find out more about the use of cookies in the
Cookie Policy.
Modification of the Privacy Policy
TESA ASSA ABLOY may modify its Privacy Policy from time to time in accordance with applicable law, In any case, any modification of the Privacy Policy will be duly notified so that you are informed of the changes made in the processing of your personal data and, if the applicable regulations so require, you can give your consent.
By clicking “Accept All Cookies”, you agree to the storing of cookies on your device to enhance site navigation, analyze site usage, and assist in our marketing efforts.
Read more about our use of cookies.
